Green Lisi Town is a 35-hectare (86-acre) mixed-use development on the lakefront of Lisi Lake in the southwest of Tbilisi, the capital of the country of Georgia. Chairman of TBC Bank, Mamuka Khazaradze's Georgian Redevelopment Company is behind the project, in partnership with FMO, the Netherlands Development Finance Company, while architectural firm Andropogon did the master plan and site design. The community mixes residential, recreational, educational, and religious uses as well as office space for artists and architects. Phase One of Green Lisi Town was already open in 2011. As of 2012, the American Academy in Tbilisi (GZAAT) is under construction in Green Lisi Town.
